[2
Date: 1 Aug 2001 18:25:15 +0400
From: Alexander Vladyko <alex@promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail Regional Moderator for NIS/CIS
Source: Website of the Health Ministry of the Russian Federation (Outbreaks
News Website, in Russian), 31 Jul & 1 Aug 2001 [edited
<http://www.depart.drureg.ru/hotline/>

According to the Center of the State Sanitary and Epidemiology Surveillance
of the Republic of Tatarstan for Tue 31 Jul 2001, 32 cases of acute
intestinal disease have been recorded in Kazan from whom, after laboratory
investigation, El-Tor vibrio, serovar Ogawa, have been isolated. [One
person was found to be a _Vibrio_ carrier. [To date, approximately 199
people have been hospitalized, [some because they were contacts of active
cases.
Appropriate prophylactic and epidemiological measures are being carried out
under the direction of Gennady Onishchenko, First Deputy Minister of the
Health Ministry and the Chief State Sanitary Physician of the Russian
Federation. Specialists from the Plaque Institutions (Russian PRI "Microb,"
Rostov PRI, and Plague Center of the Health Ministry) have been sent to
Kazan in order to provide practical help.
